articles.author: James Mackenzie
articles.description: Israel prepared on Saturday to receive six more hostages from Gaza in exchange for hundreds of Palestinian prisoners and detainees, after accusations over the return of a misidentified body this week threatened to derail a fragile truce.
articles.title: Israel prepares to receive six more Gaza hostages

articles.author: Steve Holland, Nandita Bose
articles.description: White House national security adviser Mike Waltz said on Friday he expects Ukrainian President Volodymyr Zelenskiy to sign a minerals agreement with the United States as part of efforts to end the Ukraine war, while President Donald Trump said Kyiv has no cards to play with.
articles.title: White House expects Ukraine to sign critical minerals deal soon

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: In a ruined Soviet-era apartment block in Pisky, near the east Ukrainian city of Donetsk, huge chunks of roof and walls lie scattered about the floor where Maria Seryogova once played with her baby grandson.
articles.title: Villagers in Russian-controlled Ukraine visit homes destroyed in long conflict

articles.author: Andrea Shalal, Joey Roulette
articles.description: Ukraine's access to SpaceX-owned Starlink was brought up in talks between U.S. and Ukrainian officials after Ukrainian President Zelenskiy turned down an initial proposal from U.S. Treasury Secretary Bessent.
articles.title: Exclusive: US could cut Ukraine's access to Starlink internet services over minerals, say sources

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: A second meeting between representatives of Russia and the United States is planned for the next two weeks, the RIA state news agency reported on Saturday, citing Russian Deputy Foreign Minister Sergei Ryabkov.
articles.title: Russia, U.S. representatives to meet again within two weeks, senior Russian diplomat says

articles.author: Thomas Escritt
articles.description: Germans go to the polls on Sunday in a snap election called after the collapse of Chancellor Olaf Scholz's three-way coalition. This is how Germany's election system works:
articles.title: German election: Why new voting rules make results hard to predict

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Russian Deputy Foreign Minister Sergei Ryabkov said on Saturday Moscow had not yet received agreement from Washington for its new ambassador to the United States, the RIA state news agency reported.
articles.title: Russia has yet to receive agreement for new ambassador to US, senior diplomat says

articles.author: Prasto Wardoyo
articles.description: Over two decades and 37 surgeries on, Chusnul Chotimah is still reeling from the night she survived the Bali bombing, which killed 202 in one of the world's deadliest militant attacks.
articles.title: Bali bombing survivor fears losing life-saving aid to Indonesia's budget cuts

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Australia accused China on Saturday of failing to give satisfactory reasons for what it called inadequate notice of a live-fire drill in waters between Australia and New Zealand that forced airlines to divert flights.
articles.title: Australia says China failed to explain inadequate navy live-fire notice

articles.author: Sarah Marsh
articles.description: Alice Weidel, the chancellor candidate of the far-right Alternative for Germany (AfD), is an unlikely public face for a male-dominated, anti-immigration party that depicts itself as a defender of traditional family values and ordinary people.
articles.title: German far-right leader is a Chinese-speaking economist with foreign partner
